      Jul 5, 2022Previous review

      "My birthstone is a coffee bean...okay, maybe not, but humanity runs on coffee." And, so do I. My special coffee drink is a Skinny Vanilla Latte.

      This Starbucks is so warm and welcoming. They are so kind, especially trying to understand what I want for my order, while wearing my mask.

      They have awesome baked goods and bagels. I love their scones and bagel holes-filled with cream cheese.
      The coffee is always hot and well brewed.

      The store is clean and well organized. So, if you want to start your day off right, stop by for a coffee and leave with a smile.

      Sep 1, 2018Previous review

      People will ask me, " What is your favorite drink?" I always chose coffee and Starbucks knows how to make me happy. My regular latte is the skinny vanilla latte with a blondie bean. It satisfies my caffeine craving and my sweet tooth, while not adding too many calories. If I am feeling rather indulgent, had a challenging day, or just want a special treat, I will go with the Carmel macchiato. It always makes me smile and tastes delicious. That Carmel flavor is like drinking my dessert.

      On my last visit, I discovered these bagel balls. They are about the size of a golf ball and are filled with cream cheese. Warm them up and start the day on a high note. The plus is that they are so small that the amount of calories is not too high. I try to stay away from the scones,but occasionally they slip into my order. The blueberry is so yummy.

      The service is wonderful and these people are slammed with customers most of the day. The food and drinks are beyond reproach! With my new longer commute, they will be seeing a lot more of me! Keep up the fabulous job!

    • Kim W.

      Jul 18, 2025

      Consistently Great Service and a Welcoming Atmosphere

      I never thought I'd be a regular at Starbucks with a local coffee shop right in my building--but the difference in service is night and day.

      At Starbucks, the team is always friendly, fast, and professional. They greet me by name, say good morning, and wish me a great day--small gestures that make a big difference. The mobile app is a huge plus: I can order ahead without any extra fees, and my drink is ready when I walk in.

      Even during busy times, the staff is upbeat and efficient. It's clear they value their customers and take pride in creating a good experience.

      While other places may have decent coffee, Starbucks wins with consistent quality and exceptional service. It's why I keep coming back.
